    • regroup

      public static <I, O> Stream<O> regroup(Stream<I> input, Function<I,O> makeKey, BiConsumer<O,I> collector)
      Group a stream of input and output the grouped output stream.
      Type Parameters:
      O - the output type of the grouping. It must have the following behaviour:
      • they must have a single argument constructor that selects all the group-by elements out of the input type
      • the must have additional fields to collect the grouped elements into collections
      • the must have a an {Object.equals(Object) and Object.hashCode() methods that return true if the group-by fields are identical but ignore the grouped collections
      Parameters:
      input - the stream to consume
      makeKey - the constructor that makes an output item for an input item; if it returns null, it should be skipped
      collector - a function that adds all of the collected input data to an output value
      Returns:
      the grouped output stream
